WEBVTT

00:01.479 --> 00:03.177
<i>Previously</i> <i>
on "Superman & Lois"...</i>

00:03.220 --> 00:05.527
You are what
this town needs for mayor.

00:05.570 --> 00:08.443
I know what I saw--
you and some woman.

00:08.486 --> 00:10.227
I think that
you need to move out.

00:10.271 --> 00:12.055
You're using X-K, aren't you?
You lied to me.

00:12.099 --> 00:13.535
<i>I thought you were
getting powers.</i>

00:13.578 --> 00:15.058
<i>It's not gonna</i> <i>
happen again, okay?.</i>

00:15.102 --> 00:16.625
<i>Timmy's mom found</i> <i>
an inhaler.</i>

00:16.668 --> 00:18.105
Apparently the police
are involved.

00:18.148 --> 00:19.628
It's real.

00:19.671 --> 00:21.064
<i>A different dimension,</i> <i>
a parallel universe,</i>

00:21.108 --> 00:22.457
if Ally's goal is
to use these pendants

00:22.500 --> 00:24.502
<i>to become some</i> <i>
kind of a god...</i>

00:24.546 --> 00:25.938
<i>Then I need to get it back</i> <i>
from Anderson and destroy it.</i>

00:25.982 --> 00:28.593
An unidentified
Kryptonian being

00:28.637 --> 00:30.508
took the lives
of two of our assets.

00:30.552 --> 00:33.076
Why didn't you tell me that
thing you were chasing was you?

00:33.120 --> 00:34.164
It's not me.

00:34.208 --> 00:35.600
You captured
your doppelganger?

00:35.644 --> 00:37.472
I need to understand
why he's here.

00:37.515 --> 00:40.127
You will find
that pale son of a bitch

00:40.170 --> 00:41.693
by any means necessary,

00:41.737 --> 00:44.827
or you will be stripped
of your duties.

00:44.870 --> 00:47.134
<i>Until he reveals</i> <i>
the location of that thing</i>

00:47.177 --> 00:49.049
<i>that killed our men,</i> <i>
Superman will remain</i>

00:49.092 --> 00:51.660
<i>a prisoner of</i> <i>
the United States government.</i>

01:02.540 --> 01:06.631
<i>♪</i>

01:06.675 --> 01:09.547
Look what the wind blew in.

01:09.591 --> 01:13.943
<i>♪</i>

01:13.986 --> 01:15.336
What is this?

01:15.379 --> 01:18.513
Your jackbooted friends
brought you in last night.

01:18.556 --> 01:19.427
Or was it this morning?

01:20.863 --> 01:24.780
Time loses all meaning
in captivity.

01:24.823 --> 01:27.609
I wonder, brother,
what you possibly

01:27.652 --> 01:29.611
could've done
to wind up in here?

01:29.654 --> 01:31.439
Presumably you've been
on the rough end

01:31.482 --> 01:33.876
of a rather vicious betrayal.
- Enough.

01:33.919 --> 01:37.575
I don't need to hear it
from you right now.

01:37.619 --> 01:39.577
There's been
a misunderstanding.

01:41.884 --> 01:45.061
One I'm very anxious
to hear about.

01:45.105 --> 01:49.674
<i>♪</i>

01:49.718 --> 01:53.025
Anderson.

01:53.069 --> 01:59.467
<i>♪</i>

01:59.510 --> 02:00.555
You need to let me out.

02:00.598 --> 02:02.687
Actually, I don't.

02:02.731 --> 02:05.908
I've been given full command
of this operation.

02:05.951 --> 02:09.346
Your arrest was sanctioned
by General Hardcastle herself.

02:09.390 --> 02:11.740
And given that you're actively
harboring a monster

02:11.783 --> 02:13.089
who's killed American soldiers,

02:13.133 --> 02:14.656
I think the consequences
are appropriate.

02:14.699 --> 02:15.961
Once I destroy the pendant,

02:16.005 --> 02:17.528
I will bring him in
so he can stand trial.

02:17.572 --> 02:19.182
I don't care about a trial

02:19.226 --> 02:22.620
and I don't trust you
to keep your word, so...

02:22.664 --> 02:24.405
tell me where he is.

02:27.059 --> 02:28.496
Fine.

02:28.539 --> 02:30.672
You can rot in here
with your brother.

02:33.370 --> 02:34.632
Anderson.

02:35.764 --> 02:37.157
There's a greater threat here.

02:37.200 --> 02:39.985
Her name is Ally Allston.
She's a cult leader.

02:40.029 --> 02:42.249
Whatever brought your suspect
to this world,

02:42.292 --> 02:44.076
she knows more about it
than anyone.

02:44.120 --> 02:46.253
She's dangerous, and
she needs to be stopped.

02:46.296 --> 02:48.733
If you don't believe me, then
look into her for yourself.

02:48.777 --> 02:50.605
Whoever this woman
turns out to be,

02:50.648 --> 02:52.607
it changes nothing.

02:52.650 --> 02:54.435
When I return,

02:54.478 --> 02:57.394
you will give me
the location of my suspect.

02:57.438 --> 03:01.703
<i>♪</i>

03:03.226 --> 03:06.011
Well, brother,
now that we're all alone,

03:06.055 --> 03:08.971
why don't you spin me a tale

03:09.014 --> 03:11.582
and tell me all about
this new monster you're after.

03:11.626 --> 03:18.937
<i>♪</i>

03:23.725 --> 03:25.292
<i>Clark is where?</i>

03:25.335 --> 03:30.035
The same offsite prison
where I sent Tal-Rho.

03:30.079 --> 03:32.081
Is he being questioned
or punished?

03:32.124 --> 03:33.822
And how long do they intend
to hold him?

03:33.865 --> 03:35.563
My contact didn't know

03:35.606 --> 03:38.609
but they're charging him
with treason.

03:38.653 --> 03:40.916
Treason?
That's--that's insane.

03:40.959 --> 03:42.657
He's Superman,
for God's sake.

03:42.700 --> 03:45.225
Yes, I know, but here we are,
and it doesn't sound

03:45.268 --> 03:47.357
like this is gonna get resolved
anytime soon.

03:47.401 --> 03:48.880
Well, then
I will resolve it myself.

03:48.924 --> 03:51.056
Lois, you can't just barge
into the DOD

03:51.100 --> 03:53.624
and demand Anderson
release Superman.

03:53.668 --> 03:55.147
Let me make some calls.

03:55.191 --> 03:57.715
Dad, you have been
making calls all night.

03:57.759 --> 04:00.762
We need to get him
out of there.

04:00.805 --> 04:03.330
I'll head to the DOD,
raise a little noise,

04:03.373 --> 04:05.767
see if I can get
a face-to-face with Hardcastle.

04:07.725 --> 04:10.162
Any updates on Dad?

04:10.206 --> 04:13.122
Uh, not yet.
We're working on it.

04:15.080 --> 04:16.734
Why don't you,
like, write an article

04:16.778 --> 04:18.780
about how Superman was
taken to prison by the DOD?

04:18.823 --> 04:20.695
Trust me,
they would just deny it.

04:20.738 --> 04:23.611
You guys are gonna have to keep
yourselves busy after school,

04:23.654 --> 04:25.787
okay, until your grandfather
and I figure this out.

04:25.830 --> 04:27.005
Sure.

04:27.049 --> 04:28.920
So, whatever's going on
between you two,

04:28.964 --> 04:32.097
I suggest you figure it out.

04:34.361 --> 04:35.536
Jordan.

04:38.582 --> 04:44.240
<i>♪</i>

05:00.865 --> 05:02.867
Is this the last
of Dad's stuff?

05:02.911 --> 05:05.261
Honey, you shouldn't
have to do that.

05:05.305 --> 05:07.219
I didn't really want
Sophie to see.

05:07.263 --> 05:09.091
Well, I didn't want
you to see.

05:09.134 --> 05:12.312
Well, this is
what's got to happen, right?

05:13.400 --> 05:15.837
Might as well
just get it over with.

05:17.839 --> 05:20.885
I never wanted my daughters
to know what it felt like

05:20.929 --> 05:25.281
to have a broken home,
especially coming from one.

05:25.325 --> 05:28.589
I am so sorry to put you
and your sister through this.

05:28.632 --> 05:31.853
Mom, you're not putting us
through anything.

05:31.896 --> 05:33.898
Dad is.

05:33.942 --> 05:36.074
None of this is your fault.

05:36.118 --> 05:39.556
None of it
is yours either, okay?

05:39.600 --> 05:42.385
<i>♪</i>

05:42.429 --> 05:43.908
All right, honey,
we got to go.

05:43.952 --> 05:45.867
Okay,
I'll go get Sophie ready.

05:45.910 --> 05:49.174
- Thank you.
- Sophie, school!

05:52.352 --> 05:59.359
<i>♪</i>

06:06.801 --> 06:08.324
<i>♪</i>

06:08.368 --> 06:13.024
<i>♪ Is it too soon</i> <i>
to say I love you? ♪</i>

06:13.068 --> 06:15.462
<i>♪ Is it too soon</i> <i>
to say goodbye? ♪</i>

06:15.505 --> 06:16.550
Hey.

06:16.593 --> 06:17.942
<i>♪</i>

06:17.986 --> 06:19.988
You heading to first period?

06:20.031 --> 06:21.816
I don't know yet.

06:29.127 --> 06:31.869
- Did you sleep last night?
- Not much.

06:31.913 --> 06:34.829
I just found out
my dad's moving out.

06:34.872 --> 06:36.961
So...

06:37.005 --> 06:39.834
- L-l-like, forever?
- Probably.

06:39.877 --> 06:43.446
- Maybe--
- I don't know, Jordan.

06:43.490 --> 06:45.753
Sorry,
it's only been one night,

06:45.796 --> 06:50.932
and it's just so hard seeing
my mom cry all the time.

06:50.975 --> 06:53.804
I-I can imagine.

06:55.502 --> 06:57.852
I don't really know
if you can.

06:57.895 --> 07:05.207
<i>♪</i>

07:09.820 --> 07:12.214
Hey, babe.

07:12.257 --> 07:14.912
Still thinking about
how sexy you were on the field.

07:14.956 --> 07:17.045
I did have a little help.

07:17.088 --> 07:20.048
Yeah, and it worked, so...

07:20.091 --> 07:24.008
I, uh...
I brought you some more.

07:25.880 --> 07:27.925
That should last you awhile.

07:28.970 --> 07:30.362
Candice...
- Oh, don't worry.

07:30.406 --> 07:31.929
I'll hook you up
with a good price.

07:31.973 --> 07:34.366
No, no, that's not--
it's not about that.

07:34.410 --> 07:35.672
It's just...

07:37.761 --> 07:39.023
Honestly, I think I'm done.

07:39.067 --> 07:40.460
Jon, are you
out of your mind?

07:40.503 --> 07:42.505
I can't.
I can't do that anymore.

07:42.549 --> 07:44.376
Jon, you're starting
quarterback, okay?

07:44.420 --> 07:46.857
You can't just stop. This--this
is what helped you get there.

07:46.901 --> 07:48.337
Everyone,

07:48.380 --> 07:50.165
I need you to step away
from your lockers.

07:50.208 --> 07:51.514
Oh, my God,
that's the police.

07:51.558 --> 07:53.342
- Drug dog...
- It's for the X-K.

07:53.385 --> 07:55.562
I can't get caught
with this stuff, Jonathan.

07:55.605 --> 07:58.129
The people my dad works for,
if they find out about this,

07:58.173 --> 08:01.785
we're gonna lose everything.
- Shh. No, you won't.

08:01.829 --> 08:02.960
What are you doing?

08:03.004 --> 08:04.919
I'll dump it.
I'll dump it, okay?

08:04.962 --> 08:06.137
I'm a good kid.

08:06.181 --> 08:07.574
There's no way
they're gonna check me.

08:07.617 --> 08:11.491
And if they do, then...

08:17.975 --> 08:19.716
No, Dad,
I will not hang tight

08:19.760 --> 08:20.978
and let you do your thing.

08:21.022 --> 08:22.937
Well, then go
to Hardcastle's office

08:22.980 --> 08:23.981
and kick in the door,

08:24.025 --> 08:27.158
because if you don't,
I will.

08:27.202 --> 08:29.030
Fine.
Call me back.

08:29.073 --> 08:32.816
Hey.
Are you okay?

08:32.860 --> 08:36.733
Now Dean's acting like he's
the family-values candidate?

08:36.777 --> 08:38.039
Seriously?

08:38.082 --> 08:39.649
I know.
It's absurd.

08:39.693 --> 08:41.999
But, yeah, that seems to be
the strategy they're going for,

08:42.043 --> 08:43.566
and, unfortunately,
his campaign

08:43.610 --> 08:45.089
can print whatever
message they want.

08:45.133 --> 08:47.091
I have to fight back.

08:47.135 --> 08:49.964
How much did he pay for this?

08:50.007 --> 08:52.575
- $3,000.
- I can't afford that.

08:52.619 --> 08:55.099
If it was up to me,
I would run your ads for free

08:55.143 --> 08:57.188
every single day
up until the election,

08:57.232 --> 08:59.539
but I'm afraid that
would violate

08:59.582 --> 09:02.063
every campaign finance law imaginable.

09:02.106 --> 09:03.499
So what do I do?

09:03.543 --> 09:05.719
I mean, Dean's got
the power of his office

09:05.762 --> 09:08.069
and the town gossip
all working in his favor.

09:08.112 --> 09:10.245
But you have the truth.

09:10.288 --> 09:12.073
Don't underestimate that.

09:12.116 --> 09:13.944
There's still plenty of time
to beat Dean.

09:13.988 --> 09:16.033
You just have to
catch him off guard.

09:16.077 --> 09:19.994
One sec.

09:22.344 --> 09:23.040
Hello?

09:27.001 --> 09:29.003
He was caught with what?

09:29.046 --> 09:31.266
<i>I pity you, brother.</i>

09:31.309 --> 09:34.312
I mean, after everything
you've done for humanity,

09:34.356 --> 09:37.402
to find yourself here...
- Do you ever stop talking?

09:37.446 --> 09:39.796
Cast out, imprisoned.

09:39.840 --> 09:42.364
It's humiliating.
- Yes.

09:42.407 --> 09:44.061
Well, the real punishment
is having to listen to you.

09:44.105 --> 09:47.064
Now, that is unfair.
I'm on your side.

09:47.108 --> 09:48.631
Have you so quickly forgotten

09:48.675 --> 09:50.894
the aid I provided
last time we met?

09:50.938 --> 09:53.027
You attacked my son!

09:53.070 --> 09:56.813
An overreaction, I admit,
but no harm came of it.

09:56.857 --> 09:59.947
And did I not bring you
face-to-face with our mother?

09:59.990 --> 10:02.732
For that good deed alone,
I deserve at least some credit.

10:02.776 --> 10:04.691
You got what you deserved--

10:04.734 --> 10:07.650
to be locked up in here.
- With you.

10:07.694 --> 10:10.610
Last chance, Superman.

10:12.394 --> 10:13.743
Where's my suspect?

10:13.787 --> 10:15.527
I asked you to
look into Ally Allston.

10:15.571 --> 10:17.486
If you did, then you know
what we're up against.

10:17.529 --> 10:19.662
If you didn't, then I need to
speak to General Hardcastle.

10:19.706 --> 10:21.882
I told you,
I'm in command now,

10:21.925 --> 10:24.275
and I want that thing
that killed my team.

10:24.319 --> 10:26.887
But if you won't tell me
where he is...

10:28.671 --> 10:29.933
Maybe he will?

10:29.977 --> 10:32.240
I beg your pardon?

10:35.069 --> 10:38.725
You Kryptonians must have
so many secrets.

10:38.768 --> 10:43.773
Maybe my suspect's hidey-hole
is among them?

10:43.817 --> 10:45.601
Assuming that were true,

10:45.645 --> 10:47.951
what would you offer
for my cooperation?

10:47.995 --> 10:53.348
<i>♪</i>

10:53.391 --> 10:56.220
Simple--
I'll make the pain stop.

10:57.918 --> 11:00.616
Stop, stop!

11:06.970 --> 11:08.580
Hey.

11:08.624 --> 11:10.931
Do you know anything
about Jonathan Kent

11:10.974 --> 11:12.628
taking this drug
from the mines?

11:12.672 --> 11:15.109
Whoa, can you let me
put my stuff down first?

11:15.152 --> 11:17.328
- Sarah, this is serious.
- I know.

11:17.372 --> 11:20.288
I was there
when the sheriff came in.

11:20.331 --> 11:22.159
No, I didn't know
anything about it.

11:22.203 --> 11:23.552
Thank God.

11:23.595 --> 11:26.120
Yeah.
Jordan's freaking out.

11:26.163 --> 11:27.687
Please just promise me--

11:27.730 --> 11:30.254
Not to smoke space drugs?
Yeah, I'm not that stupid.

11:35.259 --> 11:36.696
What is it?

11:36.739 --> 11:39.699
It's just dad calling
for, like, the 100th time.

11:41.135 --> 11:43.703
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

11:46.140 --> 11:47.968
No.

11:48.011 --> 11:50.797
I just feel like I can't talk
to Jordan about everything.

11:50.840 --> 11:52.189
I mean, he's sweet,

11:52.233 --> 11:54.191
but the biggest problem he has
with his dad

11:54.235 --> 11:56.933
is the coach shorts
that Mr. Kent likes to wear,

11:56.977 --> 12:00.110
and he just has a lot going on
with his family right now.

12:00.154 --> 12:02.939
He doesn't need another thing.

12:02.983 --> 12:04.636
You know, it might be good

12:04.680 --> 12:07.944
for you to just vent
to a friend a little bit.

12:07.988 --> 12:09.163
Is there anyone else

12:09.206 --> 12:11.295
you feel comfortable talking to
about this?

12:11.339 --> 12:15.430
<i>♪</i>

12:15.473 --> 12:18.346
<i>20 X-K inhalers?</i>

12:19.521 --> 12:21.784
20.
- I was getting rid of them.

12:21.828 --> 12:24.221
Do not lie to me,
Jonathan, not today!

12:24.265 --> 12:28.008
This family is going through
enough right now,

12:28.051 --> 12:31.228
and I am trying so hard

12:31.272 --> 12:33.230
to keep it together.

12:33.274 --> 12:34.797
So I'm gonna ask you,

12:34.841 --> 12:37.713
and you are gonna be honest
with me.

12:37.757 --> 12:40.107
Are you selling drugs?
- No.

12:40.150 --> 12:41.717
Mom, I promise.

12:41.761 --> 12:44.111
And it's not even
technically drugs, right?

12:44.154 --> 12:46.330
The sheriff's
not even pressing charges.

12:46.374 --> 12:47.810
Tell that to the school, Jonathan.

12:47.854 --> 12:49.464
They are meeting
right now to decide

12:49.507 --> 12:52.249
whether or not
to have you expelled!

12:52.293 --> 12:55.078
And regardless
of how you classify

12:55.122 --> 12:57.385
experimental space narcotics,

12:57.428 --> 13:00.388
what the hell were you doing
with so much of it?

13:04.348 --> 13:05.828
I can't tell you that.

13:05.872 --> 13:08.788
If you ever want to leave
this house again, you better.

13:08.831 --> 13:10.790
Mom, people are
gonna get in trouble.

13:10.833 --> 13:13.270
Yeah, drug dealers.

13:13.314 --> 13:15.490
Mom, I understand
that you're upset,

13:15.533 --> 13:17.057
but I cannot rat.

13:17.100 --> 13:20.103
Do you have any idea
how much trouble you are in?

13:20.147 --> 13:21.365
What, do you just think,

13:21.409 --> 13:23.324
"Oh, my mom will just talk
my way out of this"?

13:23.367 --> 13:25.456
I am so pissed.

13:25.500 --> 13:28.329
And, trust me, Jonathan,
your father will be, too.

13:31.201 --> 13:33.290
Were you involved in this?

13:35.989 --> 13:38.208
I, um...

13:38.252 --> 13:41.211
I found out the other night.

13:41.255 --> 13:43.823
The other night?

13:43.866 --> 13:46.173
Jordan caught me using X-K,
and he called me out.

13:46.216 --> 13:47.957
And I haven't used it since.

13:48.001 --> 13:50.742
So you were using
this stuff?

13:50.786 --> 13:54.572
<i>♪</i>

13:54.616 --> 13:56.531
For the last
couple weeks, yeah,

13:56.574 --> 13:59.316
'cause Timmy was using it,
and I just--

13:59.360 --> 14:01.841
I didn't think that
I could beat him without it.

14:04.191 --> 14:05.453
Who are you?

14:07.455 --> 14:09.196
You know what?

14:09.239 --> 14:13.417
I have had
enough disappointment

14:13.461 --> 14:14.636
for the day.

14:14.679 --> 14:17.421
So get upstairs right now,
both of you.

14:17.465 --> 14:24.776
<i>♪</i>

14:27.518 --> 14:29.259
Tell me where he is

14:29.303 --> 14:32.219
before the Kyptonite
destroys you.

14:32.262 --> 14:34.003
Anderson,
you don't understand

14:34.047 --> 14:35.439
what you're asking me to do.

14:35.483 --> 14:36.527
That suspect has knowledge

14:36.571 --> 14:38.268
we may need to
stop something terrible!

14:38.312 --> 14:41.271
I don't care.

14:41.315 --> 14:42.925
You willing to die for him?

14:42.969 --> 14:45.101
The man who put you here
in the first place?

14:45.145 --> 14:48.235
Brother, please.

14:48.278 --> 14:49.627
Enough, enough!

14:49.671 --> 14:54.241
He's at 76.2 north longitude,
100.4 west latitude.

14:54.284 --> 14:57.418
Take it off!

14:59.028 --> 15:00.987
Thank you...

15:01.030 --> 15:03.163
for your cooperation.

15:06.209 --> 15:13.260
<i>♪</i>

15:39.460 --> 15:41.723
Hey.

15:41.766 --> 15:44.552
Hey, I am sorry
to show up out of nowhere,

15:44.595 --> 15:46.336
and I know how much you're
going through right now,

15:46.380 --> 15:49.513
but I really just need to talk.
- Of course.

15:51.602 --> 15:56.259
Do you really think Jonathan
was selling X-K?

15:56.303 --> 15:57.391
He claims it wasn't his,

15:57.434 --> 15:59.349
but who knows
if he's telling the truth?

15:59.393 --> 16:01.264
He didn't even admit
he was using

16:01.308 --> 16:03.005
until his brother outed him.

16:03.049 --> 16:04.354
That's awful.

16:04.398 --> 16:06.313
What did Clark say?

16:06.356 --> 16:08.010
He doesn't know.

16:08.054 --> 16:10.143
I'm afraid
that when he finds out

16:10.186 --> 16:12.362
he's never gonna forgive him.

16:12.406 --> 16:14.582
How did I miss this?

16:14.625 --> 16:17.454
I had no idea
this was going on.

16:17.498 --> 16:20.153
You cannot blame yourself.

16:20.196 --> 16:23.983
Kids that age are--are
pretty good at keeping secrets

16:24.026 --> 16:26.115
from their parents.
- I know.

16:27.595 --> 16:31.033
I just didn't know the boys
had these kinds of secrets.

16:33.035 --> 16:35.516
Why would he do something
like that?

16:39.476 --> 16:42.001
You know...

16:42.044 --> 16:44.916
after Sarah's
suicide attempt,

16:44.960 --> 16:48.050
I kept wanting her
to tell me why she did it

16:48.094 --> 16:50.313
because that's what
I needed to hear

16:50.357 --> 16:51.923
to make myself feel better.

16:51.967 --> 16:54.404
But when we did finally talk
about it,

16:54.448 --> 16:58.495
I realized that the best thing
I could do was just listen,

16:58.539 --> 17:01.803
even if the answer
wasn't what I wanted to hear.

17:01.846 --> 17:06.199
It let her know that I was
there for her no matter what.

17:06.242 --> 17:08.853
And sometimes...

17:08.897 --> 17:11.508
that's the only job
as a mom--

17:11.552 --> 17:15.382
to be there for you kid when
they don't have anyone else.

17:15.425 --> 17:19.516
<i>♪</i>

17:19.560 --> 17:20.909
I think that Mayor Dean

17:20.952 --> 17:24.565
made a big mistake
bringing up family values.

17:24.608 --> 17:28.525
I'm pretty sure I still have
a husband that cheated on me.

17:28.569 --> 17:31.311
But you are a great mom,

17:31.354 --> 17:32.442
and accusing a good mom

17:32.486 --> 17:35.315
of being a bad one
is terrible politics.

17:35.358 --> 17:38.187
<i>♪</i>

17:38.231 --> 17:40.407
Yeah, you're right.

17:40.450 --> 17:42.800
I just need to call him out,

17:42.844 --> 17:45.412
take the fight to him.

17:49.546 --> 17:52.245
What? Is that you're supplier
freaking out?

17:52.288 --> 17:53.420
Shut up.

17:53.463 --> 17:54.812
Well, I wasn't the one

17:54.856 --> 17:56.423
selling drugs
to the football team, so...

17:56.466 --> 17:58.773
Hey, hey,
for the last time, okay,

17:58.816 --> 18:00.557
I was not selling drugs.

18:00.601 --> 18:02.168
Okay, then why'd you have
that bag full of vials?

18:02.211 --> 18:04.300
Look, I thought
that I could get rid of it,

18:04.344 --> 18:06.041
and I-I--whatever.

18:06.085 --> 18:08.130
I thought that if I got caught,
it just--it wasn't a big deal.

18:08.174 --> 18:10.437
I thought I'd be
in a little trouble.

18:10.480 --> 18:11.699
- A little trouble?
- Yes.

18:11.742 --> 18:13.440
Come on,
was it someone on the team?

18:13.483 --> 18:15.224
Was it Wellnitz?
- No, Jordan, no!

18:15.268 --> 18:16.617
It was Wellnitz.

18:16.660 --> 18:18.358
Please stop.

18:18.401 --> 18:20.011
I don't know why
you'd get in all this trouble

18:20.055 --> 18:21.535
if it was
someone else's, though.

18:21.578 --> 18:22.797
Look, I made a dumb decision.

18:22.840 --> 18:25.974
You were right,
I'm a terrible brother.

18:26.017 --> 18:28.542
Can you please
just leave me alone?

18:30.544 --> 18:32.067
Yeah.

18:32.111 --> 18:37.725
<i>♪</i>

18:40.075 --> 18:42.208
You would let them
torture me?

18:42.251 --> 18:45.689
I'm a prisoner here,
same as you.

18:45.733 --> 18:48.736
Yes, but you can secure
your own release.

18:48.779 --> 18:53.132
My fate here is
of a more permanent nature.

18:55.917 --> 18:57.136
Unless...

19:00.574 --> 19:02.619
Unless what?

19:02.663 --> 19:05.274
Well, I happen to know
a few of your little secrets,

19:05.318 --> 19:06.841
don't I?

19:06.884 --> 19:09.626
Delicate matters that I might
very well use to my advantage.

19:09.670 --> 19:11.672
<i>We are approaching</i> <i>
the target.</i>

19:11.715 --> 19:13.108
Proceed with caution.

19:13.152 --> 19:16.807
If that thing is in there,
it's extremely dangerous.

19:16.851 --> 19:19.723
<i>Appears to be empty, sir.</i>

19:19.767 --> 19:21.638
Damn it, he lied to me.

19:21.682 --> 19:22.857
Don't threaten me!

19:22.900 --> 19:24.554
You're not the one
being brought to heel

19:24.598 --> 19:26.643
by some barbarous
Kryptonite collar.

19:26.687 --> 19:27.862
Perhaps I might extend my leash

19:27.905 --> 19:30.386
by shining a light
on all your many lies.

19:30.430 --> 19:32.910
That's enough!

19:32.954 --> 19:36.087
Is it, brother?
I think not.

19:36.131 --> 19:37.698
<i>Sir, we found something.</i>

19:37.741 --> 19:40.701
<i>♪</i>

19:40.744 --> 19:42.224
<i>Any idea what this is?</i>

19:42.268 --> 19:44.705
It's that thing's suit.

19:44.748 --> 19:46.794
Superman must've warned him
that we were coming.

19:46.837 --> 19:48.361
They're working together.

19:48.404 --> 19:50.450
This whole time
Superman's been lying to me,

19:50.493 --> 19:51.538
and there's the proof.

19:51.581 --> 19:58.762
<i>♪</i>

20:19.653 --> 20:21.263
Move, move, move!

20:21.307 --> 20:24.310
Prisoners,
back away from each other now!

20:24.353 --> 20:27.226
I gave you an order!
Let him go!

20:27.269 --> 20:31.578
Prisoner, back away,
or my soldiers will open fire!

20:31.621 --> 20:34.798
Of course.
My apologies.

20:34.842 --> 20:36.713
Sir, General Hardcastle's
on line one.

20:36.757 --> 20:39.542
Says she's been trying
to reach you.

20:39.586 --> 20:42.284
Hold her off until
I have something to report.

20:42.328 --> 20:43.938
<i>♪</i>

20:43.981 --> 20:46.723
What the hell
is going on there?

20:46.767 --> 20:49.248
<i>♪</i>

20:49.291 --> 20:50.292
Is he breathing?

20:50.336 --> 20:51.946
He's Superman.
I'm sure he's fine.

20:51.989 --> 20:54.209
Check his pulse, soldier.

20:54.253 --> 20:56.429
Those are Kryptonians.
Get the men out of that cell!

20:56.472 --> 20:57.734
Sir, say it again?

20:57.778 --> 20:59.780
<i>Do not approach</i> <i>
that prisoner!</i>

20:59.823 --> 21:01.172
<i>Fall back, fall back!</i>

21:01.216 --> 21:07.918
<i>♪</i>

21:07.962 --> 21:09.703
- Don't shoot me.
- Tal.

21:09.746 --> 21:12.096
Come, now, little brother,
I played my part.

21:12.140 --> 21:14.360
At least let me
have a little fun.

21:14.403 --> 21:19.843
<i>♪</i>

21:23.412 --> 21:25.588
I've missed this feeling.

21:25.632 --> 21:28.069
<i>♪</i>

21:28.112 --> 21:30.680
Oh, look,
here comes the cavalry.

21:30.724 --> 21:33.248
I think I'll take that
as my cue.

21:33.292 --> 21:40.299
<i>♪</i>

21:48.785 --> 21:50.178
Satellite has prisoners
on course for the Badlands.

21:50.221 --> 21:51.440
That's where Superman
fought Tal-Rho.

21:51.484 --> 21:52.702
You really believe

21:52.746 --> 21:54.138
they've been working together
this whole time?

21:54.182 --> 21:55.749
How else do you explain
what we've seen?

21:55.792 --> 21:57.011
We have to presume

21:57.054 --> 21:58.404
that everything
is a part of some plot.

21:58.447 --> 21:59.883
Good luck getting the brass
to give a damn.

21:59.927 --> 22:01.015
I need a chopper
ready to go ASAP.

22:01.058 --> 22:02.625
But, sir,
General Hardcastle...

22:02.669 --> 22:03.887
She's gonna take over
my command

22:03.931 --> 22:05.193
if I don't prove
that I'm right.

22:05.236 --> 22:07.064
The best way to do that
is to finish this.

22:09.023 --> 22:11.634
What are you gonna do?

22:11.678 --> 22:12.853
Simple...

22:15.246 --> 22:18.293
I'm gonna kill the bad guys
and bring Superman back...

22:18.337 --> 22:20.774
<i>♪</i>

22:20.817 --> 22:22.776
One way or another.

22:22.819 --> 22:27.650
<i>♪</i>

22:27.694 --> 22:29.870
Tal claims the two of you
escaped a prison

22:29.913 --> 22:31.785
and have joined forces.

22:33.090 --> 22:35.266
- I had no other choice.
- It was glorious, Mother.

22:35.310 --> 22:37.443
Two sons of Krypton vanquishing

22:37.486 --> 22:38.835
their human oppressors.

22:38.879 --> 22:40.315
You'd have been proud.

22:41.011 --> 22:42.404
It's fascinating.

22:42.448 --> 22:46.147
He's like some
warped version of you.

22:50.194 --> 22:51.848
And he babbles like an idiot.

22:51.892 --> 22:54.373
His words flow backwards.

22:54.416 --> 22:55.983
Unless...

22:57.245 --> 23:00.074
- This man betrayed my family.
- Sounds familiar.

23:00.117 --> 23:02.381
Uh, I'm sure
there's more to it than that.

23:02.424 --> 23:05.122
Well, were we always
at odds on your world?

23:05.166 --> 23:06.210
No.

23:07.603 --> 23:09.779
We were inseparable.

23:09.823 --> 23:11.085
The closest of brothers.

23:11.128 --> 23:12.869
What droves us apart?

23:12.913 --> 23:15.916
Greed?
Power?

23:15.959 --> 23:18.962
Your wife tried to kill me.

23:19.006 --> 23:20.007
My wife?

23:20.050 --> 23:23.227
<i>♪</i>

23:23.271 --> 23:24.490
My wife?

23:29.146 --> 23:32.454
Thank you.

23:32.498 --> 23:35.631
Aubrey, hey.

23:35.675 --> 23:37.241
Hey.

23:38.939 --> 23:40.810
Uh...

23:40.854 --> 23:41.855
thanks for coming.

23:41.898 --> 23:43.813
I-I know that it's--
it's a long way.

23:43.857 --> 23:45.032
It wasn't that bad.

23:45.075 --> 23:48.427
Clover's only,
like, a two-hour drive.

23:50.341 --> 23:54.171
So I know that I shouldn't
have ghosted you after camp.

23:55.999 --> 23:57.914
I get it.
You have a boyfriend.

23:57.958 --> 23:59.916
You didn't want
to make it all weird.

23:59.960 --> 24:03.572
Yeah, but that doesn't mean
that it wasn't rude.

24:03.616 --> 24:04.834
Mm.

24:04.878 --> 24:06.793
I just wanted to say
I'm sorry.

24:06.836 --> 24:11.362
Okay.
Well, then apology accepted.

24:12.712 --> 24:17.020
But that's not the only reason
why you texted me.

24:17.064 --> 24:19.283
Well...

24:19.327 --> 24:22.112
my life is
kind of falling apart.

24:22.156 --> 24:24.941
My dad cheated on my mom,

24:24.985 --> 24:27.988
and I feel like you're the only
person who might understand.

24:28.031 --> 24:30.947
- - Wow.
- Okay.

24:30.991 --> 24:35.517
Um, well, child of divorce
to the rescue.

24:35.561 --> 24:38.477
Just so you know, I'm, like,
totally here for you,

24:38.520 --> 24:39.956
but can we please
order some fries?

24:40.000 --> 24:42.872
'Cause I'm literally starving.

24:45.309 --> 24:49.270
And now he just won't
stop calling.

24:49.313 --> 24:51.620
Do you want to talk to him?

24:51.664 --> 24:52.708
No.

24:54.318 --> 24:55.581
Kind of.

24:55.624 --> 24:58.192
I mean, it--it just
doesn't seem fair to my mom.

24:58.235 --> 25:00.324
But it's not about her.
It's about you.

25:00.368 --> 25:02.413
Look, after my parents split,

25:02.457 --> 25:04.851
I froze my dad out for, like,
almost an entire year.

25:04.894 --> 25:07.244
And you know what?
It didn't fix their marriage.

25:07.288 --> 25:08.811
It didn't make me
feel any better,

25:08.855 --> 25:12.467
and if anything,
it just made me angry and mean.

25:12.511 --> 25:14.425
You, mean?

25:14.469 --> 25:16.515
I got into,
like, two fights that year.

25:16.558 --> 25:18.429
Look, I actually
chipped my front tooth.

25:18.473 --> 25:20.823
It was so stupid.
- That's insane.

25:20.867 --> 25:22.085
Right.

25:22.129 --> 25:23.826
So maybe spare your teeth,

25:23.870 --> 25:27.482
and if you want to see
your dad, see your dad.

25:29.484 --> 25:31.486
You're right.

25:31.530 --> 25:32.966
You're awesome.

25:33.009 --> 25:35.838
- I'm gonna hold you to that.
- Shut up.

25:38.275 --> 25:40.103
Oh, it's also later
than I thought,

25:40.147 --> 25:43.542
so I should probably get going.

25:43.585 --> 25:45.195
I got it. Um...

25:47.850 --> 25:49.809
Okay, um...

25:49.852 --> 25:52.463
I was wondering...

25:52.507 --> 25:55.162
maybe we could be
friends again?

25:58.078 --> 26:01.124
I was hoping you'd say that.

26:03.910 --> 26:05.520
- Um...
- Bye.

26:05.564 --> 26:07.087
Bye.

26:07.130 --> 26:13.093
<i>♪</i>

26:34.331 --> 26:36.290
What now?

26:36.333 --> 26:39.249
I just wanted to say
I'm sorry about what happened.

26:40.686 --> 26:42.644
Okay, well, thank you
for saying that.

26:42.688 --> 26:45.821
And also, I-I don't think it
was Jon selling those drugs.

26:45.865 --> 26:47.997
I know he was carrying them,
but you got to believe me.

26:48.041 --> 26:50.130
I think he was just trying
to cover for somebody else.

26:50.173 --> 26:52.872
I hope you're right.

26:52.915 --> 26:55.091
But you're still in trouble
for knowing about this.

26:55.135 --> 26:57.137
Yeah, I know.

27:11.717 --> 27:14.763
Let's try this again
from the beginning.

27:17.026 --> 27:18.637
Okay.

27:20.987 --> 27:25.948
Well, I found out that Timmy
was taking X-K, and so...

27:25.992 --> 27:27.341
I got some, and I started--

27:27.384 --> 27:28.995
I started taking it
to keep up with him.

27:29.038 --> 27:31.475
And--and you're right.
it was really stupid.

27:31.519 --> 27:35.175
But I just--I really, really
wanted to start this season

27:35.218 --> 27:38.352
after everything
that happened last year.

27:38.395 --> 27:41.790
I don't know--I feel
like everybody in this family

27:41.834 --> 27:43.879
is great at something.

27:46.229 --> 27:49.363
And I just--I wanted
to be great, I guess.

27:49.406 --> 27:51.931
That doesn't justify
what I did,

27:51.974 --> 27:54.760
not at all, but it's the truth.

27:54.803 --> 27:58.459
And just so you know,
I would never sell drugs.

27:58.502 --> 28:00.809
- - I believe you, sweetie.
- I do.

28:03.769 --> 28:06.728
But I'm still
incredibly disappointed in you.

28:06.772 --> 28:09.035
Taking drugs like that
is just something

28:09.078 --> 28:13.343
I never even thought
you would consider doing.

28:13.387 --> 28:16.956
I'll make it up to you, okay?
I promise.

28:16.999 --> 28:20.220
Then start by telling me
where you got the X-K.

28:20.263 --> 28:22.613
<i>♪</i>

28:22.657 --> 28:25.747
Jon, Principal Balcomb called
me again on the way back,

28:25.791 --> 28:29.272
and unless you can prove that
those inhalers were not yours,

28:29.316 --> 28:33.146
the school board
is gonna expel you.

28:33.189 --> 28:35.583
I can't ruin
someone else's life.

28:37.150 --> 28:38.847
What about your life?

28:38.891 --> 28:40.240
Honey, I know that you think

28:40.283 --> 28:42.111
that what you are doing
is right,

28:42.155 --> 28:43.722
but sometimes in life,

28:43.765 --> 28:45.636
there are mistakes
that we cannot take back,

28:45.680 --> 28:47.856
and I assure you
this is one of them.

28:47.900 --> 28:51.033
<i>♪</i>

28:51.077 --> 28:52.992
Please just tell me.

28:53.035 --> 28:55.168
<i>♪</i>

28:55.211 --> 28:57.170
I'm sorry.

28:57.213 --> 29:00.216
<i>♪</i>

29:00.260 --> 29:02.653
So am I.

29:02.697 --> 29:05.874
I can't stop thinking that
I had a wife on your world.

29:05.918 --> 29:07.702
She must be a goddess.

29:07.746 --> 29:09.922
Any idea where I might find her
on this earth?

29:09.965 --> 29:11.097
Can we please focus?

29:11.140 --> 29:12.794
Well, at least let him
tell me her name.

29:12.838 --> 29:14.665
How long's that gonna take?
- Kal.

29:15.536 --> 29:16.798
Something is coming.

29:19.192 --> 29:20.323
It's a missile.

29:20.367 --> 29:22.325
<i>♪</i>

29:25.372 --> 29:32.422
<i>♪</i>

29:39.386 --> 29:42.258
Superman!

29:42.302 --> 29:45.131
You will stand down,
or I'll open fire.

29:45.174 --> 29:46.872
You don't have to do this.

29:46.915 --> 29:50.310
I'm bringing you in,
all of you,

29:50.353 --> 29:52.399
by any means necessary.

29:52.442 --> 29:59.754
<i>♪</i>

30:07.066 --> 30:08.415
You.

30:08.458 --> 30:10.286
<i>♪</i>

30:10.330 --> 30:12.245
You killed my team.

30:12.288 --> 30:14.160
I kill anyone
who gets in my way.

30:14.203 --> 30:21.515
<i>♪</i>

30:30.002 --> 30:32.352
Let him out of the cage.

30:32.395 --> 30:34.397
I'm not gonna do that.

30:34.441 --> 30:36.878
Fine.

30:36.922 --> 30:39.228
I'll rip him
out of there myself.

30:39.272 --> 30:41.230
<i>♪</i>

30:41.274 --> 30:43.319
I don't appreciate
intruders in my home.

30:43.363 --> 30:50.674
<i>♪</i>

31:09.955 --> 31:11.304
Tal!

31:11.347 --> 31:13.262
<i>♪</i>

31:13.306 --> 31:15.221
Help my sons.

31:15.264 --> 31:22.228
<i>♪</i>

31:40.768 --> 31:42.465
What?

31:45.425 --> 31:48.167
<i>♪</i>

31:48.210 --> 31:49.385
Mother!

31:49.429 --> 31:53.433
<i>♪</i>

31:53.476 --> 31:55.304
Kryptonite fragments
have pierced

31:55.348 --> 31:58.438
several of his vital organs.

31:58.481 --> 32:00.092
You must disintegrate them.

32:00.135 --> 32:07.186
<i>♪</i>

32:22.592 --> 32:26.205
Be precise, Kal,
or you will kill him.

32:26.248 --> 32:33.038
<i>♪</i>

32:43.222 --> 32:44.310
You did it.

32:44.353 --> 32:46.877
The Kryptonite fragments
are destroyed.

32:46.921 --> 32:48.444
No, no, he's not healing.

32:48.488 --> 32:50.838
All that time in prison
under the solar lamps...

32:55.451 --> 33:02.502
<i>♪</i>

33:24.524 --> 33:31.835
<i>♪</i>

33:49.505 --> 33:53.292
<i>♪</i>

33:57.252 --> 34:04.303
<i>♪</i>

34:31.069 --> 34:38.076
<i>♪</i>

35:16.549 --> 35:23.860
<i>♪</i>

35:24.992 --> 35:28.648
I see you brought me
back to my proper place.

35:29.649 --> 35:31.912
You knew I could never
let you go free.

35:31.955 --> 35:35.045
What a shame. We could've
conquered the world by now.

35:37.352 --> 35:39.615
You should feel better
in a couple days.

35:42.705 --> 35:44.098
My father used to say,

35:44.142 --> 35:47.275
pain was just a way
of reminding me I was alive.

35:47.319 --> 35:49.277
<i>♪</i>

35:49.321 --> 35:50.713
Quite the German.

35:50.757 --> 35:53.890
<i>♪</i>

35:53.934 --> 35:55.196
And you?

35:55.240 --> 35:58.460
Am I to assume
your misunderstanding

35:58.504 --> 36:01.594
with the humans
has been resolved?

36:01.637 --> 36:02.682
More or less.

36:02.725 --> 36:04.423
<i>♪</i>

36:04.466 --> 36:07.730
They will no doubt apologize
for their oversteps,

36:07.774 --> 36:11.038
and you will go back
to trusting them.

36:11.081 --> 36:13.127
And Anderson?

36:13.171 --> 36:15.260
Escaped...

36:15.303 --> 36:16.565
but I'll find him.

36:16.609 --> 36:19.220
What of the other you?

36:19.264 --> 36:21.570
<i>♪</i>

36:21.614 --> 36:22.658
He's dead.

36:22.702 --> 36:24.617
<i>♪</i>

36:24.660 --> 36:26.706
Could've been me tonight...

36:26.749 --> 36:28.621
if you hadn't done
what you did.

36:28.664 --> 36:30.710
Well, what are brothers for?

36:30.753 --> 36:34.583
<i>♪</i>

36:34.627 --> 36:36.498
Thank you.

36:36.542 --> 36:43.592
<i>♪</i>

36:45.028 --> 36:46.334
Kal.

36:46.378 --> 36:49.772
<i>♪</i>

36:49.816 --> 36:52.166
Tell your son I'm sorry.

36:52.210 --> 36:54.908
<i>♪</i>

36:54.951 --> 36:57.693
You know, maybe someday

36:57.737 --> 37:00.261
you can tell him yourself...

37:00.305 --> 37:01.741
brother.

37:01.784 --> 37:06.354
<i>♪</i>

37:08.400 --> 37:15.450
<i>♪</i>

37:23.197 --> 37:26.200
<i>A warrant has been issued</i> <i>
for Anderson's arrest.</i>

37:26.244 --> 37:29.290
He went AWOL,
stole government property,

37:29.334 --> 37:34.121
weapons from project 7734,
vials of confiscated X-K.

37:34.164 --> 37:36.819
And he blames Superman for
ruining his life and career.

37:36.863 --> 37:40.562
The sooner we get him
behind bars, the better.

37:40.606 --> 37:41.868
I want you to know,

37:41.911 --> 37:43.913
I offered to lead
the manhunt myself.

37:43.957 --> 37:45.654
That's not
your responsibility, Dad.

37:45.698 --> 37:47.917
You retired.
- Yeah.

37:47.961 --> 37:50.790
But I'm the one who recommended
him for the job.

37:50.833 --> 37:52.922
<i>♪</i>

37:56.839 --> 38:03.890
<i>♪</i>

38:06.632 --> 38:10.418
Long day.

38:10.462 --> 38:11.941
Sam.

38:13.160 --> 38:16.337
All I want now
is some Chinese food.

38:17.817 --> 38:20.863
A glass of red wine...

38:20.907 --> 38:22.778
be with my family.

38:22.822 --> 38:25.477
<i>♪</i>

38:25.520 --> 38:27.348
What?

38:27.392 --> 38:29.045
<i>You've always got to know</i> <i>
what's going on in your family</i>

38:29.089 --> 38:31.831
because that's what
this town is.

38:31.874 --> 38:34.703
We are all family.

38:34.747 --> 38:36.749
Hell, Chuck and I--

38:36.792 --> 38:40.056
we went to St. John Vianney
together since first grade.

38:40.100 --> 38:44.017
Aidy, we sing
next to each other

38:44.060 --> 38:45.801
every Sunday in the choir.

38:45.845 --> 38:47.716
Now, let's be honest...

38:47.760 --> 38:49.936
Aidy's beautiful voice
drowns me out,

38:49.979 --> 38:51.851
but I'm trying.

38:51.894 --> 38:54.462
I'm trying.

38:54.506 --> 38:56.595
But my point is this...

38:56.638 --> 38:59.511
if you can't keep control
of your own family,

38:59.554 --> 39:00.860
if you don't really know

39:00.903 --> 39:02.949
what's going on
in your own home,

39:02.992 --> 39:04.603
how are we supposed to trust

39:04.646 --> 39:06.431
that you'd know
what's going on with all of us?

39:06.474 --> 39:11.740
Because I love this town,
George, and everyone in it.

39:11.784 --> 39:13.263
Well, Lana...

39:13.307 --> 39:17.746
I just can't be sure,
given your current situation,

39:17.790 --> 39:19.269
if we can be sure of that.

39:19.313 --> 39:20.880
Well, I guess
I'll just have to make it clear

39:20.923 --> 39:22.577
to everybody
during our debates.

39:22.621 --> 39:25.841
But what should really be
in question here, George,

39:25.885 --> 39:28.453
is what kind of person
you are--

39:28.496 --> 39:31.847
someone so willing to attack

39:31.891 --> 39:35.155
a member of this family

39:35.198 --> 39:38.376
during one of the most painful
moments of their life.

39:38.419 --> 39:42.336
<i>♪</i>

39:42.380 --> 39:44.947
Does that sound like
family values to you?

39:44.991 --> 39:52.302
<i>♪</i>

40:05.490 --> 40:06.882
Dad.

40:06.926 --> 40:12.366
<i>♪</i>

40:12.410 --> 40:13.933
Can we talk?

40:13.976 --> 40:16.239
<i>♪</i>

40:16.283 --> 40:17.937
Yeah.

40:17.980 --> 40:24.944
<i>♪</i>

40:24.987 --> 40:26.989
You're back.

40:27.033 --> 40:28.600
Yeah, I am,
and you know what?

40:28.643 --> 40:30.558
I was not expecting to hear
what your mother just told me.

40:30.602 --> 40:32.473
- Dad, I can explain.
- Jonathan, no!

40:32.517 --> 40:34.344
Your mom gave you
multiple chances

40:34.388 --> 40:37.913
to tell her the whole story,
you chose not to.

40:37.957 --> 40:40.786
- I'm sorry.
- What were you thinking?

40:40.829 --> 40:42.701
I just--I-I wanted
to be better.

40:42.744 --> 40:45.921
By taking drugs?
Have we taught you nothing?

40:45.965 --> 40:47.445
Have not heard
a single word

40:47.488 --> 40:48.924
that either of us
has ever said to you?

40:48.968 --> 40:51.492
- Yes.
- Then, damn it, act like it.

40:51.536 --> 40:54.669
<i>♪</i>

40:54.713 --> 40:56.105
Tomorrow you will go,

40:56.149 --> 40:57.977
and you will apologize
to Principal Balcomb.

40:58.020 --> 40:59.935
Then you will apologize
to Coach Gaines,

40:59.979 --> 41:00.806
and after that,
you will apologize

41:00.849 --> 41:02.285
to the entire football team.

41:02.329 --> 41:03.939
Your mother and I are gonna
figure out

41:03.983 --> 41:05.941
how you're gonna finish out
the school year,

41:05.985 --> 41:07.943
whether it's
in the next town over,

41:07.987 --> 41:09.945
online,
or somewhere else.

41:09.989 --> 41:13.383
And after all that, Jonathan,
you and I are gonna have

41:13.427 --> 41:15.951
a long talk
about all the important things

41:15.995 --> 41:17.518
I thought you already knew

41:17.562 --> 41:20.608
so that you don't ever
misrepresent yourself

41:20.652 --> 41:22.828
or this family again.

41:22.871 --> 41:25.047
Do you understand?

41:25.091 --> 41:26.092
Yes, sir.

41:26.135 --> 41:32.794
<i>♪</i>

41:34.840 --> 41:40.019
<i>♪</i>

41:46.634 --> 41:48.506
Ally Allston.

41:50.899 --> 41:53.032
Yes?

41:53.075 --> 41:54.903
I'm Mitchell Anderson,

41:54.947 --> 41:57.950
formerly of the United States
Department of Defense.

41:57.993 --> 42:01.997
I heard about you
from Superman.

42:02.041 --> 42:05.087
From Superman.

42:05.131 --> 42:07.002
He thought you
were dangerous enough

42:07.046 --> 42:09.352
that I should look
into you...

42:09.396 --> 42:12.355
and I have something
that he wants,

42:12.399 --> 42:15.663
but I think
it belongs to you.

42:15.707 --> 42:17.360
Can you...

42:19.362 --> 42:21.843
Can you tell me what this is?

42:21.887 --> 42:26.761
<i>♪</i>

42:26.805 --> 42:28.546
That...

42:30.286 --> 42:32.941
That is the way
to change the worlds.

42:32.985 --> 42:38.294
<i>♪</i>

43:00.447 --> 43:03.319
<i>Greg, move your head.</i>
